news.title: Tesla to expand presence in Palo Alto despite HQ move to Texas: Source
news.para: Tesla's expansion in Palo Alto came even after CEO Elon Musk announced last week that the company was moving its headquarters from Palo Alto, California to Austin, Texas.

news.title: China Evergrande owes $28 million for Changchun land, says city government
news.para: Evergrande bought the land through local developer Changchun Jitao Real Estate Development Co for 601 million yuan ($93 million) in an auction on June 17, part of a series of coordinated sales by 22 of China's biggest cities.

news.title: PMC Bank fraud case: HC rejects HDIL founder's medical bail plea
news.para: A single bench presided over by Justice Nitin Sambre said that Wadhawan's submission that he was immediately required to be released on temporary bail on medical ground, was "not justified".

news.title: China real estate shares, bonds hit by Evergrande concerns
news.para: Evergrande, which has more than $300 billion in liabilities and 1,300 real estate projects in over 280 cities, missed a third round of interest payments on its international bonds this week.

news.title: Jaipur development body mulls green area in Lohamandi commercial scheme
news.para: According to the proposal, 1.40 lakh sq metre will be earmarked for parks in the scheme. The scheme with an area of 13.50 lakh sq metre, will have six parks.

news.title: Jaipur: Erstwhile royal family's property worth Rs 100 crore sold illegally, FIR filed
news.para: According to the police, the FIR was filed by one Naryan Singh on Tuesday as a caretaker for the property. The FIR alleged that some persons used fake and forged documents for the sale and transfer of the property, listed as Khasra number 428 and sold on August 27.

news.title: Risland India and Tahiliani Homes collaborates to introduce uber luxury couture homes in New Delhi
South Delhi civic body challans 72 units for flouting dust norms
news.para: “Last week, we fined 72 companies/builders/owners amounting to nearly Rs 65 lakh for violating DPCC guidelines including projects executed by the NBCC where a fine of Rs 5 lakh was imposed. ,” said the release.

news.title: Greater Noida development body to conduct survey of STPs in housing societies
news.para: The Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority (GNIDA) will check if STPs have been installed in all societies, even the ones that have secured completion certificates recently.

news.title: Gurugram: Sushant Lok RWA goes to DTCP over poor upkeep
news.para: Sushant Lok Extension includes Sushant Lok-2 and 3. In his complaint, RWA secretary R P Mittal said maintenance services in the area are pathetic, be it related to roads, sanitation, security or horticulture.

news.title: Delhi government has so far fined 165 construction sites for violation of dust norms
news.para: Under the Delhi government's anti-dust campaign, so far 522 construction sites have been inspected and fines worth Rs 53.5 lakh have been imposed on 165 of them for the violation of dust mitigation norms.

news.title: Mumbai: SCDRC directs builder to pay compensation to home buyers
news.para: ​The builder was also directed to hand over possession of the 1,070 sq ft flat in Saffire project at Magathane, hand over another flat of the same dimensions in that locality to the complainants or refund the Rs 23 lakh paid for the flat in 2013, along with 18% interest pa.

news.title: Inspire Co-spaces sets up 35,000 sq ft co-working space in Pune's Baner
news.para: It recently acquired a 50,000 sq ft space in Pune’s Kalyani Nagar, with a total capacity of 1,000 seats. Following this expansion in Pune, Inspire co-spaces has a total 6,000 seats across its co-working hubs.

news.title: Aparna Infra Housing buys two office buildings in Hyderabad for Rs 247.5 crore
news.para: The transactions, valued at Rs 247.5 crore, were carried out through Aparna’s subsidiary Hitech CyberSpazio, people aware of the development said.

news.title: ASK Group's offshore fund exits Kumar Properties' Pune project with 1.9 times returns
news.para: The fund has exited from Kumar Properties’ project Kumar Prospera in Pune's Hadapsar locality, which is surrounded by a mix of tech parks, large corporate office buildings, and exclusive gated residential complexes.
